    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "SUMMARY OF INFORMATION:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "The following information was received 12 August 1947 from [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "to the sighting of a possible flying disc 4 August 1947.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "bb",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "On 4 August 1947, [REDACTED], an [REDACTED] with Pan American",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "Airways, Inc., was the first pilot of a Constellation type aircraft on a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "flight from Gander, Newfoundland, to La Guardia Field, New York. [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "took over the aircraft at Gander, Newfoundland and departed at approximately",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "1230 P.M., Eastern Daylight Saving Time for La Guardia Field, New York. At",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "1600 P.M., at a position approximately midway between the Everett (Mass) Radio",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "Marker and the Bedford Radio Beacon (Everett is 5 miles NW of Boston, Mass.,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "and Bedford is 15 miles NW of the same city) both [REDACTED] and [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "sighted unidentifiable flying objects. To the best",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "of [REDACTED] the following weather conditions existed at that",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "time: Visibility was good; cloud coverage was from 6-8/10ths, with tops at",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "10,000 feet; and the wind at the 8,000 foot level was estimated as being",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "270/25 miles per hour. The aircraft was at 8,000 feet; airspeed 265 mph;",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "and the course was 244 degrees, magnetic.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "bb",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "[REDACTED] who was sitting in the co-pilots seat (the right side of",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "the cockpit) first called [REDACTED] attention to a bright orange object,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "which was on the right side of the plane, and slightly below the level of the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "aircraft. [REDACTED] was unable to see the object, as he had no visibility to",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "text": "the right and down, from his position. [REDACTED] immediately glanced out his",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "side window and noticed, at a 45° angle to the left, and unidentified flying",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "object. It was about one mile away at an altitude of approximately 7,800",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "text": "feet. [REDACTED] banked to obtain a better view of the object. The object",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 53,
      "text": "was under observation for approximately 30 seconds, and during this time was",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 54,
      "text": "viewed by [REDACTED]. [REDACTED] described the object as being about the length",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 55,
      "text": "of a P-40 fuselage, blunt at both ends, cylindrical in shape, and having a",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 56,
      "text": "bright orange hue. [REDACTED] stated that the object had a definite shape, and",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 57,
      "text": "that there was no suggestion of gaseous dissipation as there would be if the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 58,
      "text": "orange color were the exhaust from a rocket, or a jet aircraft. [REDACTED]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 59,
      "text": "estimated the course of the object to be 200° magnetic, and that the object",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 60,
      "text": "was travelling at approximately 150 mph. [REDACTED] lost sight of the object,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 61,
      "text": "when a cloud came between the aircraft and the object. The pursuit of the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 62,
      "text": "object was not continued, inasmuch as it would have necessitated a departure",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 63,
      "text": "from the established airways.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
